OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 22 Mar to Tue 31 MarFA
OL,6,Ftransition to a more changeable and in
OL,7,Fplaces rather unsettled spell of
OL,8,Fweather looks to take place at the
OL,9,Fstart of this period as Atlantic
OL,10,Ffrontal zones cross the UK. These are
OL,11,Flikely to be most active in the north
OL,12,Fand somewhat weaker further south,
OL,13,Fcloser to a ridge of high pressure
OL,14,Fextending northeast from the
OL,15,Fsubtropical Atlantic. It is possible
OL,16,Fthat we may see a briefly widely
OL,17,Fcolder interlude with northerly winds
OL,18,Fduring the final week of March, which
OL,19,Fwould bring the potential for some
OL,20,Fsnow, especially for northern areas.
OL,21,FWidely strong winds could also develop
OL,22,Faround this time. By the end of March,
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fhigh pressure may become rather more
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fdominant with plenty of dry weather,
OL,25,Fbut with some overnight fog and frost.
